[m[1;2;48:2:56:58:59mâ€º [22mhow do i login as an admin


[m[22;2mâ€¢ [22;94m1. [39mSet your admin password hash in root [36m.env[39m:

[m  - Generate a bcrypt hash (example for password [36mMyStrongPass123[39m):

[m  node -e "require('bcrypt').hash('MyStrongPass123', 12).then(console.log)"

[m  - Put output into:

[m  ADMIN_PASSWORD_HASH=$2b$12$...
[m  ADMIN_JWT_SECRET=some-long-random-secret
[m  ADMIN_SESSION_HOURS=24

[m  [94m2. [39mStart the app ([36mnpm run dev[39m).
[m  [94m3. [39mOpen [36mhttp://localhost:4200/admin/login[39m.
[m  [94m4. [39mEnter the [22;1mplain password[22m you hashed ([36mMyStrongPass123[39m) in the login form.

[m  The backend verifies it against [36mADMIN_PASSWORD_HASH[39m and returns a JWT; frontend
[m  stores it and grants access to [36m/admin[39m.


