[m[22;2mâ€¢ [22;36mERR_CONNECTION_REFUSED[39m means the frontend cannot reach the API at [36mhttp://
[m  [36mlocalhost:3000[39m because nothing is listening there.

[m  Do this:

[m  [94m1. [39mStart API explicitly:

[m  npm run --workspace api start:dev

[m  [94m2. [39mIn another terminal, verify health:

[m  curl http://localhost:3000/api/health

[m  You should get JSON like [36m{"status":"ok",...}[39m.

[m  [94m3. [39mKeep frontend running ([36mnpm run --workspace frontend start[39m or [36mnpm run dev[39m), then
[m     retry [36m/admin/login[39m.

[m  If API fails to boot, paste the API terminal error here. The most common next issue
[m  is missing [36m.env[39m values ([36mADMIN_PASSWORD_HASH[39m, [36mADMIN_JWT_SECRET[39m).

